obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (70865)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70865&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Punjab Land-revenue`
  line `Act, 1887.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the territories for the time being administered by the Lieutenant-Governor of the`
  line `Punjab, including the pargana of Spiti, but not so as to affect, otherwise than as`
  line `expressly provided by this`
  line `Act, any Regulation in force under the provisions of the Statute 33 Victoria, chapter 3, section 1, in any`
  line `portion of those territories; and`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such day as the Local Government, with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Governor General in Council, may by notification appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) Any power conferred by this Act on the Financial Commissioner to make rules, and on the Local`
  line `Government to sanction them, may be exercised at any time after the passing of this Ad, but a rule so`
  line `made shall not take effect till the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (70866)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70866&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) The enactments mentioned in the schedule are repealed to the extent specified in the`
  line `third column thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) But all rules, appointments, assessments and transfers made, notifications and proclamations`
  line `issued, authorities and powers conferred, farms and leases granted, records-of-rights and other records`
  line `framed, revised or confirmed, rights acquired, liabilities incurred, times and places appointed and other`
  line `things done under any of the repealed enactments shall, so far as may be, be deemed to have been`
  line `respectively made, issued, conferred, granted, framed, revised, confirmed, acquired, incurred, appointed`
  line `and done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Any enactment or document referring to any enactment hereby repealed shall be construed as`
  line `referring to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (70867)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70867&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or context,-`
  line `(1) "estate" means any area-`
  line
  line `(a) for which a separate record-of-right has been made; or`
  line
  line `(b) which has been separately assessed to land-revenue, or would have been so assessed if the`
  line `land-revenue had not been released, compounded for or redeemed; or`
  line
  line `(c) which the Local Government may, by general rule or special order, declare to be an estate:`
  line `(2) "landowner" does not include a tenant or an assignee of land-revenue, but does include a person to`
  line `whom a holding has been transferred, or an estate or holding has been let in farm, under this Act for the`
  line `recovery of an arrear of land-revenue or of a sum recoverable as such an arrear, under every other person`
  line `not here in before in this clause mentioned who is in possession of an estate or any share or portion`
  line `thereof, or in the enjoyment of any part of the profits of an estate:`
  line
  line `(3) "holding" means a share or portion of an estate held by one landowner or jointly by two or more`
  line `landowners :`
  line
  line `(4) "rent", "tenant", "landlord" and "tenancy" have the meanings respectively assigned to those words`
  line `in the Punjab tenancy Act, 1887 (XVI of 1877) :`
  line
  line `(5) "pay", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, includes, when used with reference`
  line `to rent, "deliver and render" , with their grammatical variations and cognate expressions:`
  line
  line `(6) "land-revenue" includes assigned land-revenue and any sum payable in respect of land, by way of`
  line `quit-rent or of commutation for service, to the Government or to a person to whom the Government has`
  line `assigned the right to receive the payment:`
  line
  line `(7) "arrear of land-revenue" means land-revenue which remains unpaid after the date on which it`
  line `becomes payable:`
  line
  line `(8) "defaulter" means a person liable for an arrear of land-revenue, and includes a person who is`
  line `responsible as surety for the payment of the arrear:`
  line
  line `(9) "rates and cesses" means rates and cesses which are primarily payable by landowners, and`
  line includes-
  line
  line `(a) the local rate, if any, payable under the Punjab Local Rates Act, 1878 (V of 1878);`
  line
  line `(b) the local rate, if any, payable under the Punjab District Boards Act, 1883 (XX of 1883), and any`
  line `fee leviable under section 33 of that Act from landowners for the use of or benefits derived from such`
  line `works as are referred to in section 20, clauses (i) and (j), of that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any annual rate chargeable on owners of lands under section 59 of the Northern India Canal and`
  line `Drainage Act, 1873 (VIII of 1873);`
  line
  line `(d) the zaildari and village-officers' cesses; and`
  line
  line `(e) sums payable on account of village-expenses:`
  line
  line `(10) "village-cess" includes any cess, contribution or due which is customarily leviable within an`
  line `estate and is neither a payment for the use of private property or for personal service nor imposed by or`
  line `under any enactment for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `(11) "village-officer" means a chief-headman, headman or patwari:`
  line
  line `(12) "Revenue-officer", in any provision of this Act, means a Revenue, officer having authority under`
  line `this Act to discharge the functions of a Revenue-officer under that provision:`
  line
  line `(13) "legal practitioner" means any legal practitioner with in the meaning of the Legal Practitioners`
  line `Act, 1879 (XVIII of 1879), except a mukhtar:`
  line
  line `(14) "agricultural year" means the year commencing on the sixteenth day of June, or on such other`
  line `date as the Local Government may by notification appoint for any local area:`
  line
  line `(15) "notification" means a notification published by authority of the Local Government in the official`
  line `Gazette:`
  line
  line `(16) "incumbrance" means a charge upon or claim against land arising out of a private grant or`
  line `contract: and`
  line
  line `(17) "survey-mark" includes boundary-mark`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (70868)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Exclusion of certain land from operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70868&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except so far as may be necessary for the`
  line `record, recovery and administration of viIlage-cesses, nothing in this Act applies to land which is`
  line `occupied as the site of a town or village and is not assessed to land-revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) A Revenue-officer may define for the purposes of this Act the limits of any such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (70869)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to vary limits and alter number of tahsils, districts and divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70869&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The local`
  line `Government may by notification vary the limits of the tahsils, districts and divisions into which the`
  line `territories administered by it are divided, and may by notification alter the number of those tahsils and,`
  line `with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, the number of those districts and`
  line divisions.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (70870)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Classes of Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70870&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be the following classes of Revenue-officers,`
  line namely—
  line
  line `(a) the Financial Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(b) the Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(c) the Collector;`
  line
  line `(d) the Assistant Collector of the first grade; and`
  line
  line `(e) the Assistant Collector of the second grade.`
  line
  line `(2) The Deputy Commissioner of a district shall be the Collector thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The Local Government may appoint any Assistant Commissioner, Extra Assistant Commissioner`
  line `or Tahsildar to be an Assistant Collector of the first or of the second grade, as it thinks fit, and any`
  line `Naib-tahsildar to be an Assistant Collector of the second grade.`
  line
  line `(4) Appointments under sub-section (3) shall be by notification, and may be of a person specially by`
  line `name or by virtue of his office or of more persons than one by any description sufficient for their`
  line identification.
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions or this Act the jurisdiction of the Commissioner extends to the whole of`
  line `the territories for the time being administered by the Lieutenant-Governor of the Punjab,`
  line `and of Commissioners and of Collectors and Assistant Collectors to the divisions and districts respectively in`
  line `which they are for the time being employed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (70871)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Financial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70871&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall he one or more Financial Commissioners, who shall be`
  line `appointed, and may be removed, by the Local Government with the previous sanction of the Governor`
  line `General in Council.`
  line
  line `(2) Where more Financial Commissioners than one have been appointed, the Local Government may`
  line `make rules as to the distribution among them of business under this or any other Act, and by those rules`
  line `require any case or class or classes of cases to be considered and disposed of by the Financial`
  line `Commissioners collectively.`
  line
  line `(3) When there is a difference of opinion among the Financial Commissioners as to any decree or`
  line `order to be made in a case which they are required by rules under the last foregoing sub-section to`
  line `consider and dispose of collectively, the following rules shall apply, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) where the case is an appeal or a case on review or revision, it shall be decided`
  line `in accordance with the opinion or the majority of the Financial Commissioners, or, if there is no such`
  line `majority which concurs in a decision modifying or reversing the decree or order under appeal, review`
  line `or revision, that decree or order shall be affirmed: and`
  line
  line `(b) where the case is not an appeal or a case on review or revision, the matter respecting which`
  line `there is the difference of opinion shall be referred to the Local Government for decision, and the`
  line `decision of that Government with respect thereto shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) The expression “Financial Commissioner” in this or any other Act shall, when there are more`
  line `Financial Commissioners than one, be construed as meaning one or more of the Financial`
  line `Commissioners as the rules for the time being in force under sub-section (2) may require.`
  line
  line `(5) The second Financial Commissioner appointed under section 52 of the Punjab Courts Act, 1884`
  line `(XVIII of 1884), shall be deemed to have had jurisdiction on and after the first Day of November, 1884,`
  line `to make any decree or order or dispose of any other business which might have been made or disposed of`
  line `by the other Financial Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (70872)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appointment of Commissioners, and Deputy, Assistant and Extra Assistant Commissioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70872&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Commissioners, Deputy Commissioners, Assistant Commissioners and Extra`
  line `Assistant Commissioners shall be appointed and may be removed by the Local Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (70873)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Appointment of Tahsildars and Naib-tahsildars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70873&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Local Government shall fix the number of`
  line `Tahsildars and Naib-tahsildars to be appointed, and the Financial Commissioner may make rules for their`
  line `appointment and removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (70874)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers of Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70874&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Except where the class of the Revenue-officer by whom any`
  line `function is to be discharged is specified in this Act, the Local Government may by notification determine`
  line `the functions to be discharged under this Act by any class of Revenue-officers.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (70875)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Superintendence and control of Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70875&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner shall be`
  line `subject to the control of the Local Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The general superintendence and control over all other Revenue-officers shall be vested in, and all`
  line `such officers shall be subordinate to, the Financial Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general superintendence and control of the Financial Commissioner, a`
  line `Commissioner shall control all other Revenue-officers in his division`
  line
  line `(4) Subject as aforesaid and to the control of the Commissioner, a Collector shall control all other`
  line `Revenue-officers in his district.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (70876)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to distribute business and withdraw and transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70876&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial`
  line `Commissioner or a Commissioner or Collector may by written order distribute, in such manner as he`
  line `thinks fit, any business cognizable by any Revenue-officer under his control.`
  line
  line `(2) The Financial Commissioner or a Commissioner or Collector may withdraw any case pending`
  line `before any Revenue-officer under his control, and either dispose of it himself, or by written order refer it`
  line `for disposal to any other Revenue-officer under his control.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not empower any officer to exercise any`
  line `powers or deal with any business which he would not be competent to exercise or deal with within the`
  line `local limits of his own jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (70877)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70877&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided by this Act, an appeal shall lie form an original or appellate`
  line `order of a Revenue-officer as follows, namely :—`
  line
  line `(a) to the Collector when the order is made by an Assistant Collector of either grade;`
  line
  line `(b) to the Commissioner when the order is made by a Collector;`
  line
  line `(c) to the Financial Commissioner when the order is made by a Commissioner.`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(i) when an original order is confirmed on first appeal, a further appeal`
  line `shall not lie;`
  line
  line `(ii) when any such order is modified or reversed on appeal by the Collector, the order made by the`
  line `Commissioner on further appeal, if any, to him shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (70878)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Limitation for appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70878&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided by this Act, the period of limitation for an`
  line `appeal under the last foregoing section shall run from the date of the order appealed against, and shall be`
  line `as follows, that is to say:-`
  line
  line `(a) When the appeal lies to the Collector—thirty days.`
  line
  line `(b) when the appeal lies to the Commissioner—sixty days;`
  line
  line `(c) when the appeal lies to the Financial Commissioner—ninety`
  line days.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (70879)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Review by Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70879&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue-officer may, either of his own motion or on the`
  line `application of any party interested, review, and on so reviewing modify, reverse or confirm, any order`
  line `passed by himself or by any of his predecessors in office:`
  line
  line `Provided as follows:—`
  line
  line `(a) when a Commissioner or Collector thinks it necessary to review any order which he has not`
  line `himself passed, and when a Revenue-officer of a class below that of Collector proposes to review any`
  line `order, whether passed by himself or by any of his predecessors in office, he shall first obtain the`
  line `sanction of the Revenue-officer to whose control he is immediately subject;`
  line
  line `(b) an application for review of an order shall not be entertained unless it is made within ninety`
  line `days from the passing of the order, or unless the applicant satisfies the Revenue-officer that he had`
  line `sufficient cause for not making the application within that period;`
  line
  line `(c) an order shall not be modified or reversed unless reasonable notice has been given to the parties`
  line `affected thereby to appear and be heard in support of the order;`
  line
  line `(d) an order against which an appeal has been preferred shall not be reviewed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, the Collector shall be deemed to be the successor in office of any`
  line `Revenue-officer of a lower class who has left the district or has ceased to exercise powers as a`
  line `Revenue-officer and to whom there is no successor in office.`
  line
  line `(3) An appeal shall not lie from an order refusing to review or confirming on review a previous order.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (70880)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to call for, examine and revise proceedings of Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70880&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial`
  line `Commissioner may at any time call for the record of any case pending before, or disposed of by, any`
  line `Revenue-officer subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) A Commissioner or Collector may call for the record of any case pending before, or disposed of`
  line `by, any Revenue-officer under his control.`
  line
  line `(3) If in any case in which a Commissioner or Collector has called for a record he is of opinion that the`
  line `proceedings taken or order made should be modified or reversed, he shall report the case with his opinion`
  line `thereon for the orders of the Financial Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) The Financial Commissioner may in any case called for by himself under sub section (1) or`
  line `reported to him under sub-section (3) pass such order as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not under this section pass an order reversing or modifying any proceeding or`
  line `order subordinate Revenue officer and affecting any question of right between private persons without`
  line `giving those persons an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (70881)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to make rules as to procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70881&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) the Local Government may make rules consistent`
  line `with this Act for regulating the procedure of Revenue-officers under this Act in cases in which a`
  line `procedure is not prescribed by this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The rules may provide, among other matters, for the mode of enforcing orders of ejectment from,`
  line `and delivery of possession of, immovable property, and rules providing for those matters may confer on a`
  line `Revenue-officer all or any of the powers in regard to contempts, resistance and the like which a Civil`
  line `Court may exercise in the execution of' a decree whereby it has adjudged ejectment from, or delivery of`
  line `possession of, such property.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the rules under this section, a Revenue-officer may refer any case which he is`
  line `empowered to dispose of under this Act to another Revenue-officer for investigation and report, and may`
  line `decide the case upon the report.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (70882)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Persons by whom appearances and applications may be made before and to Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70882&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Appearances before a Revenue-officer, and applications to and acts to be done before him,`
  line `under this Act may be made or done-`
  line
  line `(a) by the parties themselves, or`
  line
  line `(b) by their recognized agents or a legal practitioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that the employment of a recognized agent or legal practitioner shall not excuse the personal`
  line `attendance of a party to any proceeding in any case in which personal attendance is specially required by`
  line `an order of the officer`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), recognized agents shall be such persons as the Local`
  line `Government may by notification declare in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The fees of a legal practitioner shall not be allowed as costs in any proceeding before a`
  line `Revenue-officer under this Act unless that officer considers, for reasons to be recorded by him in writing,`
  line `that the fees should be allowed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (70883)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of Revenue-officer to summon persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70883&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue-officer may summon any`
  line `person whose attendance he considers necessary for the purpose of any business before him as a`
  line Revenue-officer.
  line
  line `(2) A person so summoned shall be bound to appear at the time and place mentioned in the summons`
  line `in person or, if the summons so allows, by his recognized agent or a legal practitioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The person attending in obedience to the summons shall be bound to state the truth upon any`
  line `matter respecting which he is examined or makes statements, and to produce such documents and other`
  line `things relating to any such matter as the Revenue-officer may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (70884)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Mode of service of summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70884&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) A summons issued by a Revenue-officer shall, if practicable,`
  line `be served (a) personally on the person to whom it is addressed, or failing him on (b) his recognized agent`
  line `or (c) an adult male member of his family usually residing with him.`
  line
  line `(2) If service cannot be so made, or if acceptance of service so be made is refused, the summons may`
  line `be served by positing a copy thereof at the usual or last known place of residence of the person to whom it`
  line `is addressed, or, if that person does not reside in the district in which the Revenue-officer is employed and`
  line `the case to which the summons relates has reference to land in that district, then by posting a copy of the`
  line `summons on some conspicuous place in or near the estate wherein the land is situate.`
  line
  line `(3) If the summons relates to a case in which persons having the same interest are so numerous that`
  line `personal service on all of them is not reasonably practicable, it may, if the Revenue-officer so directs, be`
  line `served by delivery of a copy thereof to such of those persons as the Revenue-officer nominates in this`
  line `behalf and by proclamation of the contents thereof for the information of the other persons interested.`
  line
  line `(4) A summons may, if the Revenue-officer so directs, be served on the person named therein, either`
  line `in addition to, or in substitution for, any other mode of service, by forwarding the summons by post in a`
  line `letter addressed to the person and registered under Part III of the Indian Post Office Act, 1866 (XIV of`
  line `1866).`
  line
  line `(5) When a summons is so forwarded in a letter and it is proved that the letter was properly addressed`
  line `and duly posted and registered, the Revenue-officer may presume that the summons was served at the`
  line `time when the letter would be delivered in the ordinary course of post.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (70885)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Mode of service of notice, order or proclamation or copy thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70885&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `A notice, order or`
  line `proclamation, or copy of any such document, issued by a Revenue-officer for service of any person shall`
  line `be served in the manner provided in the last foregoing section for the service of a summons.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (70886)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Mode of making proclamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70886&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `When a proclamation relating to any land is issued by a`
  line `Revenue-officer, it shall, in addition to any other mode of publication which may be prescribed in any`
  line `provision of this Act, be made by beat of drum or other customary method, and by the posting of a copy`
  line `thereof on a conspicuous place in or near the land to which it relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (70888)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Place of sitting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70888&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) An Assistant Collector may exercise his powers under this Act at any place`
  line `within the limits of the district in which he is employed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any other Revenue-officer may only exercise his powers under this Act within the local limits of`
  line `his jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (70889)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Holidays.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70889&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner, with the approval of the Local Government, shall`
  line `publish in the local official Gazette before the commencement of each calendar year a list of days to be`
  line `observed in that year as holidays by all or any Revenue-officers.`
  line
  line `(2) A proceeding had before a Revenue-officer on a day specified in the list as a day to be observed by`
  line `him as a holiday shall not be invalid by reason only of its having been had on that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (70890)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Discharge of duties of Collector dying or being disabled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70890&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `When a Collector dies or is disabled`
  line `from performing his duties, the officer who succeeds temporarily to the chief executive administration of`
  line `the district under any order which may be generally or specially issued by the Local Government in this`
  line `behalf shall be deemed to be a Collector under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (70891)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Retention of powers by Revenue-officers on transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70891&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `When a Revenue-officer of any class`
  line `who has been invested under the foregoing provisions of this Act with any powers to be exercised in any`
  line `local area is transferred from that local area to another as a Revenue-officer of the same or a higher class,`
  line `he shall continue to exercise those powers in that other local area unless the Local Government otherwise`
  line `directs or has otherwise directed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (70892)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Conferment of powers of Revenue-officers .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70892&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may by notification`
  line `confer on any person—`
  line
  line `(a) all or any of the powers of a Financial Commissioner, Commissioner or Collector under this`
  line `Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) all or any of the powers with which an Assistant Collector may be invested thereunder`
  line `and may by notification withdraw any powers so conferred.`
  line
  line `(2) A person on whom powers are conferred under sub-section (1) shall exercise those powers within`
  line `such local limits and in such classes of cases as the Local Government may direct, and, except as`
  line `otherwise directed by the local Government, shall for all purposes connected with the exercise thereof be`
  line `deemed to be a Financial Commissioner, Commissioner, Collector or Assistant Collector, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(3) If any of the powers of a Collector under this Act are conferred on an Assistant Collector, they`
  line `shall, unless the Local Government by special order otherwise directs, be exercised by him subject to the`
  line `control of the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (70893)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Rules respecting kanungos, zaildars, inamdars and village-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70893&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial`
  line `Commissioner may make rules to regulate the appointment, duties, emoluments, punishment, suspension`
  line `and removal of Kanungos, Zaildars, inamdars and village-officers.`
  line
  line `(2) Rules under sub-section (1) may direct that the emoluments of a zaildar, inamdar or village-officer`
  line `shall be such a percentage payable out of the land-revenue as may be prescribed by the rules, and that,`
  line `where the land-revenue has been released, compounded for or redeemed, the percentage shall be a charge`
  line `payable by the person who would be liable for the land-revenue if it had not been released compounded`
  line `for or redeemed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (70894)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Village-officers’ cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70894&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may by notification impose on any estates, or`
  line `on all or any local area, a cess, to be called the village-officers’ cess, at a rate not exceeding one anna for`
  line `every rupee of the annual value, for remunerating village-officers and for defraying other expenditure`
  line `directly connected with the supervision of those officers or with the`
  line `performance of their duties.`
  line
  line `(2) “Annual value” in the last foregoing sub-section has the meaning assigned to that expression in the`
  line `Punjab District Board Act, 1883 (XX of 1883).`
  line
  line `(3) The Financial Commissioner may make rule for the collection, control and expenditure of the`
  line `village-officers’ cess.`
  line
  line `(4) All cesses now levied in any local area for the purposes mentioned in sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `deemed to have been lawfully imposed and shall, until the village-officers’ cess is imposed in that local`
  line `area under that sub-section, be deemed to be lawfully leviable and, for the purposes of this section, to be`
  line `that cess.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (71036)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Restriction on attachment or assignment of remuneration of kanungos, Zaildars, Inamdars and village-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71036&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The emoluments of a Kanungo, Zaildar, inamdar or village-officers shall not`
  line `be liable to attachment in execution of a decree or`
  line `order of any Civil or Revenue Court.`
  line
  line `(2) An assignment of or charge on, or an agreement to assign or charge, any such emoluments shall be`
  line `void unless it is authorized by rules made by the Financial Commissioner in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (70897)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Record-of-rights and documents included therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70897&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided by this`
  line `Chapter, there shall be record-of-rights for each estate.`
  line
  line `(2) The record-of-rights for an estate shall include the following documents, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) statements showing, so far as may be practicable:—`
  line
  line `(i) the persons who are landowners, tenants or assignees of land-revenue in the estate, or who`
  line `are entitled to receive any of the rents, profits or produce of the estate or to occupy land therein;`
  line
  line `(ii) the nature and extent of the interests of those persons, and the conditions and liabilities`
  line `attaching thereto; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the rent, land-revenue, rates, cesses or other payments due from and to each of those`
  line `persons and to the Government ;`
  line
  line `(b) a statement of customs respecting`
  line `rights and liabilities in the estate;`
  line
  line `(c) a map of the estate; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other documents as the Financial Commissioner may, with the pervious sanction of the`
  line `Local Government, prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (70898)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Making or special revision of record-of-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70898&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) When it appears to the Local Government`
  line `that a record-of-rights for an estate does not exist, or that the existing record-of-rights for an estate`
  line `requires special revision, the Local Government may by notification direct that a record-of-rights be made`
  line `or that the record-of-rights be specially revised, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The notification may direct that records-of-rights shall be made or specially revised for all or any`
  line `estates in any local area.`
  line
  line `(3) A record-of-rights made or specially revised for an estate under this section shall be deemed to be`
  line `the record-of-rights for the estate, but shall not affect any presumption in favour of the Government which`
  line `has already arisen from any previous record-of-rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (70899)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Annual record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70899&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector shall cause to be prepared by the patwari of each estate`
  line `yearly, or at such other intervals as the Financial Commissioner may prescribe, an edition of the`
  line `record-of-rights amended in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) This edition of the record-of-rights shall be called the annual record for the estate, and shall`
  line `comprise the statements mentioned in sub-section (2), clause (a), of section 31 and such other documents,`
  line `if any, as the Financial Commissioner may, with the previous sanction of the Local Government,`
  line prescribe.
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of the preparation of the annual record, the Collector shall cause to be kept up by`
  line `the patwari of each estate a register of mutations and such other registers as the Financial Commissioner`
  line `may prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (71037)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Making of that part of the annual record which relates to land-owners, assignees of revenue and occupancy, tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71037&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person acquiring, by inheritance, purchase, mortgage, gift or`
  line `otherwise, any right in an estate as a landowner, assignee of land-revenue or tenant having a right of`
  line `occupancy, shall report his acquisition of the right to the patwari of the estate.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person acquiring the right is a minor or otherwise disqualified, his guardian or other person`
  line `having charge of his property shall make the report to the patwari.`
  line
  line `(3) The patwari shall enter in his register of mutations every report made to him under sub-section (1)`
  line `or sub-section (2), and shall also make an entry therein respecting the acquisition of any such right as`
  line `aforesaid which he has reason to believe to have taken place, and of which a report should have been`
  line `made to him under one or other of those sub-sections and has not been so made.`
  line
  line `(4) A Revenue-officer shall from time to time inquire into the correctness of all entries in the register`
  line `of mutations and into all such acquisitions as aforesaid coming to his knowledge of which, under the`
  line `foregoing sub-sections, report should have been made to the patwari and entry made in that register, and`
  line `shall in each case make such order as he thinks fit with respect to the entry in the annual record of the`
  line `right acquired.`
  line
  line `(5) Such an entry shall be made by the insertion in that record of a description of the right acquired`
  line `and by the omission from that record of any entry in any record previously prepared which by reason of`
  line `the acquisition has ceased to be correct.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (70901)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Making of that part of the annual record which relates to other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70901&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The acquisition of`
  line `any interest in land other than a right refered to in sub-section (1) of the last foregoing section shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if it is undisputed, be recorded by the patwari in such manner as the Financial Commissioner`
  line `may by rules, in this behalf prescribe; and,`
  line
  line `(b) if it is disputed, be entered by the patwari in the register of mutations and dealt with in the`
  line `manner prescribed in sub-sections (4) and (5) of the last foregoing section.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (70902)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Determination of disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70902&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) If during the making, revision or preparation of any record or in`
  line `the course of any inquiry under this Chapter a dispute arises as to any matter of which an entry is to be`
  line `made in a record or in a register of mutations, a Revenue-officer may of his own motion, or on the`
  line `application of any party interested, but subject to the provisions of the next following section, and after`
  line `such inquiry as he thinks fit, determine the entry to be made as to that matter.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such dispute the Revenue-officer is unable to satisfy himself as to which of the parties`
  line `thereto is in possession of any property to which the dispute relates, he shall ascertain by summary`
  line `inquiry who is the person best entitled to the property, and shall by order direct that that person be put in`
  line `possession thereof, and that an entry in accordance with that order be made in the record or register.`
  line
  line `(3) A direction of a Revenue-officer under sub-section (2) shall be subject to any decree or order`
  line `which may be subsequently passed by any Court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (70903)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Restrictions on variation of entries in records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70903&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Entries in records-of-rights or in annual`
  line `records, except entries made in annual records by Patwaris under clause (a) of section 35 with respect to`
  line `undisputed acquisitions of interest referred to in that section, shall not be varied in subsequent records`
  line `otherwise than by—`
  line
  line `(a) making entries in accordance with facts proved or admitted to have occurred;`
  line
  line `(b) making such entries as are agreed to by all the parties interested therein or are supported by a`
  line `decree or order binding on those parties;`
  line
  line `(c) making new maps where it is necessary to make them`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (70904)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title Mutation-fees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70904&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may fix a scale of fees for all or any classes of entries`
  line `in any record or register under this Chapter and for copies of any such entries.`
  line
  line `(2) A fee in respect of any entry shall be payable by the person in whose favour the entry is made`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (70905)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Penalty for neglect to report acquisition of any right referred to in section 34.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70905&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `neglecting to make the report required by section 34 within three months from the date of his acquisition`
  line `of a right referred to in that section shall be liable, at the discretion of the Collector, to a fine not`
  line `exceeding five times the amount of the fee which would have been payable according to the scale fixed`
  line `under the last foregoing section if the acquisition of the right had been reported immediately after its`
  line accrual.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (70906)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Obligation to furnish information necessary for the preparation of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70906&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `whose rights, interests or liabilities are required to be entered in any record under this Chapter shall be`
  line `bound to furnish, on the requisition of any Revenue-officer or village-officer engaged in compiling the`
  line `record, all information necessary for the correct compilation thereof`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (70907)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Rights of the Government in mines and minerals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70907&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `All mines of metal and coal, and all earth-oil`
  line `and gold washing shall be deemed to be the property of the Government for the purposes of the State and`
  line `the State Government shall have all powers necessary for the proper enjoyment of the Government’s right`
  line thereto.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (70908)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Presumption as to ownership of forests, quarries and waste-lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70908&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) When in any record-ofrights completed before the eighteenth day of November, 1871, it is not expressly provided that any`
  line `forest, quarry, unclaimed, unoccupied, deserted or wasteland, spontaneous produce or other accessory`
  line `interest in land belongs to the landowners, it shall be presumed to belong to the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) When in any record-of-rights completed after the date it is not expressly provided that any forest or`
  line `quarry or any such land or interest belongs to the Government, it shall be presumed to belong to the`
  line landowners.
  line
  line `(3) The presumption created by`
  line `sub-section (1) may be rebutted by showing—`
  line
  line `(a) from the records or report made by the assessing officer at the time of assessment, or`
  line
  line `(b) if the record or report is silent, then from a comparison between the assessment of villages in`
  line `which there existed, and the assessment of villages of similar character in which there did not exist,`
  line `any forest or quarry, or any such land or interest, that the forest, quarry, land or interest was taken into`
  line `account in the assessment of the land-revenue.`
  line
  line `(4) Until the presumption is so rebutted, the forest, quarry, land or interest shall be held to belong to`
  line `the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (70909)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Compensation for infringement of rights of third parties in exercise of a right of the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70909&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the exercise of any right of the Government referred to in either of the`
  line `two last foregoing sections, the rights of any person are infringed by the occupation or disturbance of the`
  line `surface of any land, the Government shall pay, or cause to be paid, to that person compensation for the`
  line infringement.
  line
  line `(2) The compensation shall be determined as nearly as may be in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Land Acquisition Act, 1870 (X of 1870).`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (70910)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Presumption in favour of entries in records-of-rights and annual records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70910&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `An entry made in`
  line `a record-of-rights in accordance with the law for the time being in force, or in an annual record in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and the rules thereunder, shall be presumed to be true until`
  line `the contrary is proved or a new entry is lawfully substituted therefor`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (70911)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Suit for declaratory decree by person aggrieved by an entry in a record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70911&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `considers himself aggrieved as to any right of which he is in the possession by an entry in a`
  line `record-of-rights or in an annual record, he may institute a suit for a declaration of his right under Chapter`
  line `VI of the Specific Relief Act, 1877 (I of 1877)`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (70912)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to make rules respecting records and other matters connected therewith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70912&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Financial Commissioner may make rules.—`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the language in which records and registers under this Chapter are to be made;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribing the form of those records and registers, and the manner in which they are to be`
  line `prepared, signed and attested;`
  line
  line `(c) for the survey of land so far as may be necessary for the preparation and correction of those`
  line `records and registers;`
  line
  line `(d) for the conduct of inquiries by`
  line `Revenue-officers under this Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(e) generally for the guidance of Revenue-officers and village-officers in matters pertaining to`
  line `records and registers mentioned or referred to in this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (70913)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Record-of-rights and annual records for groups of estates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70913&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner`
  line `may direct that a record-of-rights be made for any group of neighboring estates instead of separately for`
  line `each of the estates.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Chapter with respect to a record-of-rights and annual record for and estate`
  line `shall then, so far as they can be made applicable, apply to a record-of-rights and annual record for a group`
  line `of estates.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (70916)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Assessment of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70916&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) All land, to whatever purpose applied and wherever situate, is`
  line `liable to the payment of land-revenue to the Government, except such land as has been wholly exempted`
  line `from that liability by special contract with the Government or by the provisions of any law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Land-revenue may be assessed in cash or in kind, or partly in cash and partly in kind, as the Local`
  line `Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) Land may be assessed to land-revenue notwithstanding that that revenue, by reason of its having`
  line `been assigned, released compounded for or redeemed is not payable to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (70919)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Notification of intended re-assessment and instructions, as to principles of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70919&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `general re-assessment of the land-revenue of a district or tahsil shall not be undertaken without the`
  line `previous sanction`
  line `of the Governor General in Council and notification of that sanction.`
  line
  line `(2) In granting the sanction the Governor General in Council may prescribe such principles of`
  line `assessment and give such other instructions as he thinks fit`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (70920)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Mode of determining assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70920&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assessment shall be made by a`
  line Revenue-officer.
  line
  line `(2) Before making it that officer shall report his proposed method of assessment for the sanction of the`
  line `Financial Commissioner in such form as the Financial Commissioner, with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Local Government, may prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (70921)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Announcement of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70921&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Revenue-officer has obtained the sanction of the`
  line `Financial Commissioner to his proposed method of assessment, he shall make an order determining the`
  line `assessment proper for each estate and announce it in such manner as the Local Government may`
  line prescribe.
  line
  line `(2) At the time of Announcing the assessment he shall also declare the date from which it is to take`
  line `effect, and, subject to the other provisions of this Act, it shall take effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (70922)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Application for re-consideration of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70922&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The landowner may, within thirty days`
  line `from the date of the announcement of the assessment, present a petition to the Revenue-officer for a`
  line `reconsideration of the amount, form or conditions of the assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the land-revenue is assigned, the assignee thereof may within thirty days from that date`
  line `present a like petition to the Revenue-officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The order passed by the Revenue-officer on the petition shall set forth his reasons for granting or`
  line `refusing it.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (70923)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Confirmation and duration of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70923&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) An assessment of the land-revenue of a district`
  line `or tahsil shall not be considered final until it has been`
  line `confirmed by the Local Government.`
  line
  line `(2) At any time before an assessment is so confirmed the Commissioner or Financial Commissioner`
  line `may modify the assessment of any estate in the district or tahsil.`
  line
  line `(3) The Local Government shall, when confirming an assessment under sub-section (1), fix the period`
  line `for which the assessment is to be in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (70924)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Assessment to remain in force till new assessment takes effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70924&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the`
  line `expiration of the period fixed for the continuance of an assessment under sub-section (3) of the last`
  line `foregoing section, the assessment shall remain in force till a new assessment takes effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (70925)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Refusal to be liable for assessment and consequence thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70925&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time within ninety`
  line `days from the date of the announcement of an assessment the landowner or, where there are more`
  line `landowners than one, any of them who would be individually or collectively liable for more than half the`
  line `sum assessed may give notice to the Revenue-officer of refusal to be liable for the assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Revenue-officer receives a notice under sub-section (1), the Collector may take`
  line `possession of the estate and deal with it, as nearly as may be, as if the annulment of the assessment`
  line `thereof had been ordered as a process for the recovery of an arrear of land-revenue due thereon.`
  line
  line `(3) While the estate is in the possession of the Collector, the landowner or landowners shall be entitled`
  line `to receive from the Government an allowance, to be fixed by the Financial Commissioner, which shall not`
  line `be less than five or more than ten per cent. of the net income realized by the Government from the estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (70926)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Distribution of the assessment of an estate over the holdings comprised therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70926&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `assessment announced under section 51 is in whole or in part a fixed assessment of an estate for a term of`
  line `years, the Revenue-officer shall, before the date on which the first installment thereof becomes payablemake an order distributing it over the several holdings comprised in the estate and make and publish`
  line `a record of the distribution.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector may for sufficient reason make an order revising that record at any time while the`
  line `assessment continues to be in force, and publish the record so revised.`
  line
  line `(3) If the assessment announced under section 51 is in the form of rates chargeable according to the`
  line `results of each year or harvest, a Revenue-officer shall from year to year or from harvest to harvest, as the`
  line `conditions of the assessment may require, make and publish, not later than one month before the first`
  line `installment of the land-revenue falls due, a record of the amount payable in respect of each holding.`
  line
  line `(4) The Financial Commissioner may make rules for the guidance of Revenue-officers in making,`
  line `publishing and revising records under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (70927)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Application for amendment of the distribution of an assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70927&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person affected by`
  line `a record made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) of the last foregoing section, or by the revision of a`
  line `record under sub-section (2) of that section, may, within thirty days from the date of the publication of the`
  line `record, present a petition to the Revenue-officer for a re-consideration of the record so far as it affects`
  line him.
  line
  line `(2) The order passed by the Revenue-officer on the petition shall set forth reasons for granting or`
  line `refusing it.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (70928)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Appeals from orders under sections 52 and 57.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70928&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `An appeal from an order under the last`
  line `foregoing section or section 52 shall lie to the Commissioner, and from the appellate order of the`
  line `Commissioner to the Financial Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (70929)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Special assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70929&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Special assessment may be made by Revenue-officers in the following`
  line `cases, namely`
  line
  line `(a) when estates are formed under the next following section ;`
  line
  line `(b) when lands-revenue which has been released or assigned is resumed ;`
  line
  line `(c) when the waste-lands are sold, leased or granted by the`
  line `Government ;`
  line
  line `(d) when the assessment of any land has been annulled or the landowner has refused to be liable`
  line `therefor, and the term for which the land was to be managed by the Collector or his agent or let in farm`
  line `has expired ;`
  line
  line `(e) when assessments of land-revenue require revision in consequence of the action of water or`
  line `sand or of calamity of season or from any other cause ;`
  line
  line `(f) when revenue due to the Government on account or pasture or other natural products of land, or`
  line `on account of mills, fisheries or natural products of water, or on account of other rights described in`
  line `section 41 or section 42, has not been included in an assessment made under the foregoing provision`
  line `of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Financial Commissioner may make rules for the guidance of Revenue-officers in making`
  line `special assessments, and may confirm such assessments.`
  line
  line `(3) The foregoing provisions of this Chapter with respect to general assessments shall, subject to such`
  line `modifications thereof as the Financial Commissioner may prescribe by rules under the last foregoing`
  line `sub-section, regulate the procedure of Revenue-officers making special assessments.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (70930)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Formation of waste-land into separate estates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70930&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) When in the opinion of the Collector or of an`
  line `officer making a general re-assessment of land-revenue under the foregoing provisions of this Chapter,`
  line `the waste-land belonging to or adjoining an estate is so extensive as to exceed the requirements of the`
  line `owners of the estate with reference to pasturage or other useful purpose, the Collector or officer may at`
  line `any time, with the previous sanction of the Financial Commissioner, make a separate assessment of the`
  line `waste-land which he considers to be so in excess, and offer that land at that assessment, for such term and`
  line `on such conditions as he thinks fit, to the owners of the estate to which it belongs, and, if they refuse the`
  line `offer, to the owners of any estate which the land adjoins, and, if they also refuse the offer, to any other`
  line person.
  line
  line `(2) When the owners of the estate to which the waste-land belongs refuse the offer, the Collector shall`
  line `assign to them an annual allowance not less than five and not more than ten per cent. of the net income`
  line `realized by the Government form the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (70931)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Security for payment of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70931&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of every estate, the entire estate and the`
  line `landowner or, if there are more than one, the landowners jointly or severally shall be liable for the`
  line `land-revenue for the time being assessed on the estate :`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) the Local Government, with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, may by`
  line `notification declare that in any estate a holding or its owner shall not be liable for any part of the landrevenue for the time being assessed on the estate except that part which is payable in respect of the`
  line `holding; and`
  line
  line `(b) when there superior and inferior landowners in the same estate, the Financial Commissioner`
  line `may by rule, or by special order in each case, determine weather the superior or inferior landowners`
  line `shall be liable for the land-revenue, or weather both shall be so liable and, if so, in what proportions.`
  line
  line `(2) A notification under proviso (a) to sub-section (1) may have reference to any single estate or to any`
  line `class of estates or estates generally in any local area.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (70932)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Further security for payment of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70932&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The land-revenue for the time being`
  line `assessed on an estate or payable in respect of a holding shall be the first charge upon the rents, and`
  line `produce thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Without the previous consent of the Collector, the rents, profits or produce of an estate or holding`
  line `shall not be liable to be taken in execution of a decree or order of any Court until the land-revenue`
  line `chargeable against the rents, profits or produce, and any arrear of land-revenue due in respect of the estate`
  line `or holding, have been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (70933)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Orders to regulate payment of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70933&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in any record-ofrights, the Financial Commissioner may fix the number and amount of the installments, and the times,`
  line `places and manner, by, at and in which land-revenue is to be paid.`
  line
  line `(2) Until the Financial Commissioner otherwise directs, land-revenue shall be payable by the`
  line `installments, at the times and places and in the manner by, at and in which it is payable at the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (70934)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Rules to regulate collection, remission and suspension of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70934&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial`
  line `Commissioner may make rules consistent with this Act to regulate the collection, remission and`
  line `suspension of land-revenue, and may by those rules determine the circumstances and terms in and on`
  line `which assigned land revenue may, be collected by the assignee;`
  line
  line `(2) Where land-revenue due to an assignee is collected by a Revenue-officer, there shall be deducted`
  line `from the sum collected such a percentage on account of the cost of collection as the Financial`
  line `commissioner may by rule in this behalf prescribe.`
  line
  line `(3) A suit for an arrear of assigned land-revenue shall not be entertained unless there is annexed to the`
  line `plaint at the time of the presentation thereof a document under the hand of the Collector specially`
  line `authorizing the institution of the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (70935)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Costs recoverable as part of arrear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70935&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `The costs of any process issued under this Chapter shall be`
  line `recoverable as part of the arrear of land-revenue in respect of which the process was issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (70936)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Certified account to be evidence as to arrear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70936&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `A statement of account certified by a Revenueofficer shall be conclusive proof of the existence of an arrear of land-revenue, of its amount and of the`
  line `person who is the defaulter.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (70937)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Processes for recovery of arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70937&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions of this Act, an arrear of`
  line `land-revenue may be recovered by any one or more of the`
  line `following processes, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) by service of writ of demand on the defaulter;`
  line
  line `(b) by arrest and detention of his person;`
  line
  line `(c) by distress and sale of his movable property and uncut or ungathered crops;`
  line
  line `(d) by transfer of the holding in respect of which the arrear is due;`
  line
  line `(e) by attachment of the estate or holding in respect of which the arrear is due;`
  line
  line `(f) by annulment of the assessment of that estate or holding;`
  line
  line `(g) by sale of that estate or holding;`
  line
  line `(h) by proceeding against other immovable property of the defaulter.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (70938)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Writ of demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70938&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `A writ of demand may be issued by a Revenue-officer on or after the day`
  line `following that on which an arrear of land-revenue accrues.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (70939)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Arrest and detention of defaulter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70939&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time after an arrear of land-revenue has accrued a`
  line `Revenue-officer may issue a warrant directing an officer named therein to arrest the defaulter and bring`
  line `him before the Revenue-officer`
  line
  line `(2) When the defaulter is brought before the Revenue-officer, the Revenue-officer may cause him to`
  line `be taken before the Collector, or may keep him under personal restraint for a period not exceeding ten`
  line `days and then, if the arrear is still unpaid, cause him to be taken before the Collector.`
  line
  line `(3) When the defaulter is brought before the Collector, the Collector may issue an order to the officer`
  line `in charge of the civil jail of the district, directing him to confine the defaulter in the jail for such period,`
  line `not exceeding one month from the date of the order, as the Collector thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The process of arrest and detention shall not be executed against a defaulter who is a female,`
  line `a minor, a lunatic or idiot.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (70940)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Distress and sale of moveable property and crops.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70940&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time after an arrear of`
  line `land-revenue has accrued, the moveable property and uncut or un-gathered crops of the defaulter may be`
  line `distrained and sold by order of a Revenue-officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The distress and same shall be conducted, as nearly as may be, in accordance with the law for the`
  line `time being enforced for the attachment and sale of moveable property under the decree of a Revenue`
  line `Court constituted under the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (XVI of 1887):`
  line
  line `Provided that, in addition to the particulars exempted by that law from liability to sale, so much of the`
  line `produce of the land of the defaulter as the Collector things necessary for seed-grain and for the`
  line `subsistence, until the harvest next following, of the defaulter and his family, and of any cattle exempted`
  line `by that law, shall be exempted from sale under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (70941)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Transfer of holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70941&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time after an arrear of land-revenue has accrued on a holding,`
  line `the Collector may transfer the holding to any person being a landowner of the estate in which the holding`
  line `is situate and not being a defaulter in respect of his own holding, on condition of his paying the arrear`
  line `before being put in possession of the holding, and on such further conditions as the Collector may see fit`
  line `to prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) The transfer may, as the collector thinks fit, be either till the end of the agricultural year in which`
  line `the defaulter pays to the transferee the amount of the arrear which the transferee paid before being put in`
  line `possession of the holding, or for a term not exceeding fifteen years from the commencement of the`
  line `agricultural year next following the date of the transfer.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector shall report to the Financial Commissioner any transfer made by him under this`
  line `section, and the Financial Commissioner may set aside the transfer or alter the conditions thereof, or pass`
  line `such other order as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) A transfer under this section shall not affect the joint and several liability of the landowners of the`
  line `estate in which it is enforced.`
  line
  line `(5) In respect of all rights and liabilities arising under this Act the person to whom the holding is`
  line `transferred shall, subject to the conditions of the transfer, stand in the same position as that in which the`
  line `defaulter would have stood if the holding had not been transferred.`
  line
  line `(6) When the transfer was for a term, the holding shall, on the expiration of the term, be restored by`
  line `the Collector to the defaulter free of any claim on the part of the Government or the transferee for any`
  line `arrear of land-revenue or rates and cesses due in respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (70942)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Attachment of estate or holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70942&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time after an arrear of land-revenue has accrued,`
  line `the Collector may cause the estate or holding in respect of which the arrear is due to be attached and taken`
  line `under his own management or that of an agent appointed by him for that purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector or the agent shall be bound by all the engagements which existed between the`
  line `defaulter and his tenants, if any, and shall be entitled to manage the land and to receive all rents and`
  line `profits accruing therefrom to the exclusion of the defaulter until the arrear has been satisfied, or until the`
  line `Collector restores the land to the defaulter.`
  line
  line `(3) All surplus profits of the land attached beyond the cost of attachment and management and the`
  line `amount necessary to meet the current demand for land-revenue and rates and cesses shall be applied in`
  line `discharge of the arrear.`
  line
  line `(4) Land shall not be attached for the same arrear for a longer term than five years from the`
  line `commencement of the agricultural year next following the date of the attachment, but, if the arrear is`
  line `sooner discharged, the land shall be released and the surplus, receipts, if any, made over to the`
  line landowner
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (70943)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Annulment of assessment of estate or holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70943&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an arrear of land-revenue has been`
  line `due for a longer period than one month, and the foregoing processes are not deemed sufficient for the`
  line `recovery thereof, the financial Commissioner may, in addition to or instead of all or any of those`
  line `processes, order the existing assessment of the estate or holding in respect of which the arrear is due to be`
  line annulled.
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section shall not be put in force for the recovery of an arrear of land-revenue`
  line `which has accrued on land —`
  line
  line `(a) while under attachment under the last foregoing section, or`
  line
  line `(b) while under the charge of the Court of Wards.`
  line
  line `(3) When the assessment of any land has been annulled, the Collector may, with the previous sanction`
  line `of the Financial Commissioner, either manage the land himself or through an agent, or let it in farm to any`
  line `person willing to accept the farm, for such term and on such conditions as may be sanctioned by the`
  line `Financial Commissioner:`
  line `Provided that the term for which land may be so managed or farmed shall not be longer than fifteen`
  line `years from the commencement of the agricultural year next following the date of the annulment.`
  line
  line `(4) at some time before the expiration of that term the Collector shall determine the assessment to be`
  line `paid in respect of the estate or holding for the remainder of the term of the current assessment of the`
  line `district or tehsil, and, when that assessment has been sanctioned by the Financial Commissioner, shall`
  line `announce it to the landowner.`
  line
  line `(5) The landowner may give notice to the Collector of refusal to be liable for the assessment within`
  line `thirty days from the date on which the assessment was announced to him.`
  line
  line `(6) If notice is so given, the Collector may, with the previous sanction of the Financial Commissioner,`
  line `take the estate or holding under direct management or farm it for the remainder of the term of the current`
  line `assessment of the district or tehsil, or for any period within that term which the Financial Commissioner`
  line `may fix.`
  line
  line `(7) When the assessment of a holding is annulled, the joint responsibility of the other landowners of`
  line `the estate for the land-revenue of that holding becoming due after the annulment shall be in abeyance`
  line `until the a new assessment takes effect.`
  line
  line `(8) The Financial Commissioner may direct that any contract made by the defaulter, or by any person`
  line `through whom the defaulter claims, with respect to any land comprised in an estate or holding of which`
  line `the assessment has been annulled shall not be binding on the Collector or his agent or farmer during the`
  line `period for which the estate or holding remains under the management of the Collector or his agent or is let`
  line `in farm`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (70944)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Proclamation of attachment or annulment of assessment, and consequences of the proclamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70944&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any land is attached under section 72, or when the assessment of any land has`
  line `been annulled under the last foregoing section, the Collector shall make`
  line `proclamation thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) No payment made by any person to the defaulter before the making of the proclamation on`
  line `account of rent or any other asset in anticipation of the usual time for the payment shall, without the`
  line `special sanction of the Collector, be credited to that person or relieve him from liability to make the`
  line `payment to the Collector or his agent or farmer.`
  line
  line `(3) No payment made after the making of the proclamation on account of rent or any other asset of the`
  line `estate or holding to any person other than the Collector or his agent or farmer shall be credited to the`
  line `person making the payment or relieve him from liability to make the payment to the Collector or his agent`
  line `or farmer.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (70945)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Sale of estate or holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70945&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `When an arrear of land-revenue has accrued and the foregoing`
  line `processes are not deemed sufficient for the recovery thereof, the Collector, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the Financial Commissioner, may, in addition to, or instead of, all or any of those processes, and subject`
  line `to the provisions hereinafter contained, sell the estate or holding in respect of which the arrear is due :`
  line
  line `Provided that land shall not be sold for the recovery of—`
  line
  line `(a) any arrear which has accrued while the land was under the charge of the Court of Wards, or was`
  line `so circumstanced that the Court of Wards might have exercised`
  line `jurisdiction over it under the`
  line `provisions of section 35 of the Punjab Laws Act, 1872, (IV of 1872) clause (a), (b), (c) or (d); or`
  line
  line `(b) any arrear which has accrued while the land was under attachment under section 72 of this`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) any arrear which has accrued while the land was held under direct management by the Collector`
  line `or in farm by any other person, under section 73, after either an annulment of assessment or a refusal`
  line `to be liable therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (70946)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Effect of sale on encumbrances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70946&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Land sold under the last foregoing section shall be sold free`
  line `of all incumbrances; and all grants and contracts previously made by any person other than purchaser in`
  line `respect of the land shall become void as against the purchaser at the sale.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect—`
  line
  line `(a) a tenant’s right of occupancy, unless the right was created by the defaulter himself, or`
  line
  line `(b) any lease at fair rent, temporary or perpetual, for the erection of a dwelling-house or`
  line `manufactory, or for a mine, garden, tank, canal, place of worship, or burial ground, so long as the land`
  line `continues to be used for the purpose specified in the lease, or`
  line
  line `(c) any incumbrance, grant, contract or right of occupancy specially saved by order of the Financial`
  line `Commissioner and proclaimed as hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (70947)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Proceedings against other immoveable property of defaulter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70947&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the arrear cannot be`
  line `recovered by any of the processes hereinbefore provided, or if the Financial Commissioner considers the`
  line `enforcement of any of those processes to be inexpedient, the Collector may, where the defaulter owns any`
  line `other estate or holding, or any other immovable property, proceed under the provisions of this Act against`
  line `that property as if it were the land in respect of which the arrear is due:`
  line
  line `Provided that no interest save those of the defaulter alone shall be so proceeded against, and no`
  line `incumbrances created, grants made or contracts entered into by him in good faith shall be rendered invalid`
  line `by reason only of his interests being proceeded against.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Collector determines to proceed under this section against immovable property other`
  line `than the land in respect of which the arrear is due, he shall issue a proclamation prohibiting the transfer or`
  line `charging of the property.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector may at any time by order in writing withdraw the proclamation, and it shall be`
  line `deemed to be withdrawn when either the arrear has been paid or the interests of the defaulter in the`
  line `property have been sold for the recovery of the arrear.`
  line
  line `(4) Any private alienation of the property, or of any interest of the defaulter therein, whether by sale,`
  line `gift, mortgage or otherwise, made after the issue of the proclamation and before the withdrawal thereof`
  line `shall be void.`
  line
  line `(5) In proceedings against property under this section the Collector shall follow, as nearly as the nature`
  line `of the property will admit, the procedure prescribed for the enforcement of process against land on which`
  line `an arrear of land-revenue is due.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (70948)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Remedies open to person denying his liability for an arrear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70948&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in`
  line `section 66, when proceedings are taken under this Act for the recovery of an arrear, the person against`
  line `whom the proceedings are taken may, if he denies his liability for the arrear or any part thereof and pays`
  line `the same under protest made in writing at the time of payment and signed by him or his agent, institute a`
  line `suit in a Civil Court for the recovery of the amount so paid.`
  line
  line `(2) A suit under sub-section (1) must be instituted in a Court having jurisdiction in the place where the`
  line `office of the Collector of the district in which the arrear or some part thereof accrued is situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (70950)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Proclamation of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70950&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the receipt of the sanction of the Financial Commissioner to the`
  line `sale of any immovable property, the Collector shall issue a proclamation of the intended sale, specifying –`
  line
  line `(a) the date, time and place of the sale;`
  line
  line `(b) the property to be sold, and, if it is an estate or holding, the land-revenue assessed thereon or`
  line `payable in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) if the property is to be sold for the recovery of an arrear due in respect thereof, the`
  line `incumbrances, grants, contracts and rights of occupancy, if any, specially saved by order of the`
  line `Financial Commissioner under section 76, sub-section (2), clause (c);`
  line
  line `(d) if the property is to be sold otherwise than for the recovery of an arrear due in respect thereof`
  line `any incumbrance, grant or contract to which the property is known to be liable; and`
  line
  line `(e) the amount for the recovery of which the sale is ordered.`
  line
  line `(2) The proclamation shall also state that any person intending to claim a right of pre-emption must, on`
  line `pain of forfeiting the right, give notice of his intention to the Collector on an office-day before that fixed`
  line `for the sale.`
  line
  line `(3) The place of sale specified under clause (a) of sub-section (1) must be either the office of the`
  line `Collector or some place appointed by the Collector in this behalf and situate in or near the property to be`
  line sold.
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (70951)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Indemnity to Revenue-officer with respect to contents of proclamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70951&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `A Revenue-officer`
  line `shall not be answerable for any error, mis-statement or omission in any proclamation under the last`
  line `foregoing section, unless the same has been committed or made dishonestly.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (70952)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Publication of proclamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70952&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of the proclamation shall be served on the defaulter`
  line `and be posted in a conspicuous part of the office of the Tahsildar of the tahsil in which the property is to`
  line `be sold is situate .`
  line
  line `(2) After a copy of the proclamation has been served on the defaulter and posted in the office of the`
  line `Tahsildar, a copy thereof shall be posted in the office of the Collector.`
  line
  line `(3) The proclamation shall be further published in manner prescribed in section 22 and in such other`
  line `manner as the Collector thinks expedient.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (70953)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Time and conduct of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70953&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sale shall not take place on a Sunday or other holiday, or till`
  line `after the expiration of at least thirty days from the date on which the copy of the proclamation was posted`
  line `in the office of the Collector.`
  line
  line `(2) The sale shall be by public auction and shall be conducted either by the Collector in person or by a`
  line `Revenue-officer specially appointed by him in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (70954)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Power to postpone sale.`
  content `The Collector may from time to time postpone the sale.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70954&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (70955)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Stay of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70955&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `If at any time before the bidding at the auction is completed the defaulter pays the`
  line `arrears in respect of which the property has been proclaimed for sale, together with the costs incurred for`
  line `the recovery thereof, to the officer conducting the sale, or proves to the satisfaction of that officer that he`
  line `has already paid the same either at the place and in the manner prescribed under section 63 or into the`
  line `Government treasury, the sale shall be stayed.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (70956)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Payment of deposit by highest bidder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70956&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `When the highest bid at the auction has been ascertained`
  line `the person who made that bid shall, on the requisition of the officer conducting the sale, pay to that officer`
  line `a deposit of twenty-five per centum on the amount of his bid, and shall, on payment thereof, be declared`
  line `to be the purchaser subject to the provisions of this Chapter with respect to the exercise of any right of`
  line pre-emption.
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (70957)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Consequences of failure to pay deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70957&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `If the person who made the highest bid fails to pay the`
  line `deposit as required by the last foregoing section, the property shall forthwith be put up again and sold, and`
  line `all expenses attending the first sale, and the deficiency of price, if any, which may happen on the resale,`
  line `may be recovered from him by the Collector as if the same were an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (70958)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Exercise of right of pre-emption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70958&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time before the close of the day on which the sale`
  line `takes place any person who has given notice of his intention to claim a right of pre-emption under`
  line `section 79, sub-section (2), may, on payment to the officer conducting the sale of a deposit of twenty-five`
  line `per centum on the highest bid made at the sale, claim to take the property at that bid.`
  line
  line `(2) If the right is not disputed, he shall be declared to be the purchaser.`
  line
  line `(3) If the right is disputed, the Collector shall inquire into and decide the dispute and declare the`
  line `purchaser, and his decision and declaration shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (70959)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Time for payment in full.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70959&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `The full amount of the purchaser-money shall be paid by the`
  line `purchaser before the close of the fifteenth day from that on which the purchaser was declared.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (70960)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Procedure in default of payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70960&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `In default of payment of the full amount of the purchasemoney within the period mentioned in the last foregoing section, the deposit referred to in section 85 or`
  line `section 87, as the case may be, shall, after defraying the expenses of the sale, be forfeited to the`
  line `Government and may, if the Collector, with the previous sanction of the Commissioner, so directs, be`
  line `applied in reduction of the arrear, and the property shall be re-sold, and the defaulting purchaser shall`
  line `have no claim to the property or to any part of the sum for which it may subsequently be sold.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (70961)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Report of sale to Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70961&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Every sale of immoveable property under this Chapter shall`
  line `be reported by the Collector to the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (70962)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Application to set aside sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70962&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time within thirty days from the date of sale,`
  line `application may be made to the Commissioner to set aside the sale on the ground of some material`
  line `irregularity or mistake in publishing or conducting it.`
  line
  line `(2) But a sale shall not be set aside on that ground unless the applicant proves to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Commissioner that he has sustained substantial injury by reason of the irregularity or mistake.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (70963)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Order confirming or setting aside sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70963&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the expiration of thirty days from the date of`
  line `the sale, if such application as is mentioned in the last foregoing section has not been made, or if such`
  line `application has been made and rejected, the Commissioner shall make an order confirming the sale, and,`
  line `if such application has been made and allowed, the Commissioner shall make an order setting aside the`
  line sale.
  line
  line `(2) An order made under this section shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (70964)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Refund of purchase-money on setting aside of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70964&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the sale of any property is set`
  line `aside, the purchaser shall be entitled to receive back his purchase-money.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (70965)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Proclamation after postponement or on re-sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70965&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `A sale made after a postponement under`
  line `section 83, and a re-sale consequent on a purchaser’s default under section 89 or on the setting aside of a`
  line `sale under section 92, shall be made after the issue of a fresh proclamation in the manner hereinbefore`
  line `prescribed for the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (70966)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `On confirmation of sale, possession and certificate to be granted to purchaser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70966&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) After a`
  line `sale has been confirmed in manner aforesaid, the Collector shall put the person declared to be the`
  line `purchaser into possession of the property sold, and shall grant him a certificate to the effect that he has`
  line `purchased that property.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate shall state whether or not the property was sold for the recovery of an arrear due in`
  line `respect thereof, and if it was so sold, shall set forth the incumbrances, grants, contracts and rights of`
  line `occupancy, if any, specified in the proclamation of the sale as specially saved by order of the Financial`
  line `Commissioner under section 76, sub-section (2) , clause (c).`
  line
  line `(3) The certificate shall be deemed to be a valid transfer of the property but need not to be registered`
  line `as a conveyance.`
  line
  line `(4) Any suit brought in any Court against the certified purchaser on the ground that the purchase was`
  line `made on behalf of a person other than the certified purchaser shall be dismissed`
  line `with costs.`
  line
  line `(5) The certified purchaser of any immovable property shall be entitled to all rents and profits falling`
  line `due in respect of the property after the date of the confirmation of the sale and be liable for all instalments`
  line `of land-revenue and rates and cesses falling due in respect thereof after that date.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (70967)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Proceeds of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70967&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a sale of immoveable property under this Chapter has been`
  line `confirmed, the proceeds of the sale shall be applied in the first place to the payment of any arrears,`
  line `including costs incurred for the recovery thereof, due to the Government from the defaulter at the date of`
  line `the confirmation of the sale, whether the arrears are of land-revenue, or of sums recoverable as arrears of`
  line `land-revenue, and the surplus, if any, shall be paid to the person whose property has been sold, or, if the`
  line `property sold was owned by more than one person, then to the owners either collectively or according to`
  line `the amount of their recorded interests, as the Collector thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The surplus shall not, except under an order of a Court, be paid to any creditor of a person whose`
  line `property has been sold.`
  line
  line `(3) If the proceeds of the sale fall short of such arrears as are referred to in sub-section (1), the balance`
  line `remaining due from the defaulter may be recovered from him by further proceedings under this Chapter`
  line `or by any other means authorized by law.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (70968)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Recovery of certain arrears through Revenue-officer instead of by suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70968&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `When a village-officer`
  line `required by rules under section 28 to collect any land-revenue or sum recoverable as an arrear of landrevenue satisfies a Revenue-officer that the revenue or sums has fallen due and has not been paid to him,`
  line `the Revenue-officer may, subject to any rules which the Financial Commissioner may make in this behalf,`
  line `recover it is if it were an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (70969)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Other sums recoverable as arrears of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70969&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `In addition to any sums recoverable as`
  line `arrears of land-revenue under this Act or any other enactment for the time being in force, the following`
  line `sums may be so recovered, namely : —`
  line
  line `(a) fees, fines, costs and other charges, including the village-officers’ cess, payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) revenue due to the Government on account of pasture or other natural products of land, or on`
  line `account of mills, fisheries or natural products of water, or on account of other rights described in`
  line `section 41 or section 42 in cases in which the revenue so due has not been included in the assessment of`
  line `an estate;`
  line
  line `(c) fees payable to district boards or local boards under section 33 of the Punjab Districts Boards`
  line `Act, 1883 (XX of 1883), for the use of or benefits derived from such works as are referred to in section`
  line `20, clauses (i) and (j) , of that Act;`
  line
  line `(d) sums leviable by or under the authority of the Government as water-rates, or on account of the`
  line `maintenance or management of canals, embankments or other irrigation-works, not being sums`
  line `recoverable as arrears of land-revenue under any enactment for the`
  line `time being in force ; and`
  line
  line `(e) Sums payable to the Government by a person who is surety for the payment of any of the foregoing`
  line `sums or of any other sum recoverable as an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (70970)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Application of Chapter VI to sums recoverable under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70970&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of`
  line `Chapter VI shall, with respect to any sum mentioned or referred to in this Chapter, apply, so far as they`
  line `can be made applicable, as if the sum were an arrear of land-revenue and the person from whom, either as`
  line `principal or as surety, it is due were a defaulter in respect of such an arrear.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless any such sum is declared by any enactment for the time being in force to be recoverable as`
  line `if it were an arrear of land-revenue due in respect of the land charged therewith, the provisions of`
  line `section 77 shall apply under sub-section (1) to the recovery thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (71034)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Power of Financial Commissioner to make rules for demarcation of boundaries and erection of survey-marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71034&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner may make rules as to the manner in which`
  line `the boundaries of all or any estates in any local area are to be demarcated and as to the survey-marks to be`
  line `erected within those estates.`
  line
  line `(2) Rules under this section may prescribe, among other matters, the forms of survey-marks and the`
  line `material to be used in their construction.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (70972)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power of Revenue-officers to define boundaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70972&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue-officer may, for the purpose`
  line `of framing any record or making any assessment under this Act, or on the application of any person`
  line `interested, define the limits of any estate, or of any holding, field or other portion of an estate, and may,`
  line `for the purpose of indicating those limits, require survey-marks to be erected or repaired.`
  line
  line `(2) In defining the limits of any land under sub-section (1), the Revenue-officer may cause`
  line `survey-marks to be erected on any boundary already determined by, or by order of, any Court,`
  line `Revenue-officer or Forest settlement-officer, or restore any survey-marks already set up by, or by order`
  line `of, any Court or any such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (70973)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Cost of erection and repair of survey-marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70973&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules which the Financial`
  line `Commissioner may make in this behalf, survey-marks shall be erected and kept in repair by or at the cost`
  line `of the persons interested in the land for the indication of the limits of which they are`
  line `required:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Local Government may in any case direct that the cost of erection shall be borne by`
  line `the Government or be paid out of the proceeds of the village-officers’ cess.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (70974)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Recovery of cost incurred by the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70974&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the persons interested in the land fail to`
  line `erect or repair a survey-mark within thirty days from the date of their being required by a Revenue-officer`
  line `to do so, the Revenue-officer may cause it to be erected or repaired.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Revenue-officer causes a survey-mark to be erected or repaired, he shall, subject to any`
  line `rules or direction under the last foregoing section, apportion the cost amongst the persons interested in the`
  line `land in such manner as he deems just, and certify the same to the Collector.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector may recover the cost as if it were an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (70975)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Power of Revenue-offices to enter on land for purposes of survey and demarcation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70975&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `Revenue-officer, and any person acting under the orders of a Revenue-officer, may, in the discharge of`
  line `any duty under this Act, enter upon and survey land and erect survey-marks thereon and demarcate the`
  line `boundaries thereof, and do all other acts necessary for the proper performance of that duty`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (70976)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Surveys for purpose of preparation of records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70976&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any land is being surveyed in`
  line `pursuance of rules under section 46, clause (c), any Revenue-officer directing the survey may, by notice`
  line `or proclamation, require all persons having rights or interests in the land to indicate, within a specified`
  line `time, by temporary marks of a kind to be described in the notice or proclamation, the limits of those rights`
  line `or interests.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person to whom the notice or proclamation is addressed fails to comply with the requisition, he`
  line `shall be liable at the discretion of the Revenue-officer to fine, which may extend to ten rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (70977)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Provision of flag holders and chainmen for those surveys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70977&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of the survey of`
  line `any land in pursuance of rules under section 46, clause (c), the land-owners shall be bound to provide fit`
  line `persons to act as flag holders and chainmen.`
  line
  line `(2) If the land-owners fail to provide such persons or to provide them in sufficient number, such other`
  line `persons as a Revenue-officer considers necessary may be employed and the cost of employing them`
  line `recovered from the land-owners as if it were an arrear of land-revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (70978)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Professional surveys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70978&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it is necessary to make a survey by other agency than that of`
  line `Revenue-officers or village-officers, the`
  line `Local Government may publish a notification stating—`
  line
  line `(a) the local area to be surveyed and the nature of the survey;`
  line
  line `(b) the names or official designations of the officers by whom the survey is to be made; and`
  line
  line `(c) the kind of survey-marks to be erected by those officers.`
  line
  line `(2) From the date of the notification the officers specified therein, and the persons acting under their`
  line `orders, shall have for the purposes of the survey the powers conferred on Revenue-officers by`
  line `section 104.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (70979)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Penalty for destruction, injury or removal of survey-marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70979&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person willfully`
  line `destroys or injures or without lawful authority removes a survey-mark lawfully erected, he may be`
  line `ordered by a Revenue-officer to pay such fine not exceeding fifty rupees for each mark so destroyed,`
  line `injured or removed as may, in the opinion of the Revenue-officer, be necessary to defray the expense of restoring the same and of rewarding the person, if any, who gave information of the destruction, injury or`
  line removal.
  line
  line `(2) The imposition of a fine under this section shall not bar a prosecution under section 434 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (70980)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Report of destruction or removal of or injury to survey-marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70980&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `Every village-officer of an`
  line `estate shall be legally bound to furnish a Revenue-officer with information respecting the destruction or`
  line `removal of, or any injury done to, any survey-mark lawfully erected in the estate.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (70983)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Effect of partitions of estates and tenancies on joint liability for revenue and rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70983&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `partition of land, either under this Chapter or otherwise, shall not, without the express consent of the`
  line `Financial Commissioner, affect the joint liability of the land or of the land-owners thereof for the revenue`
  line `payable in respect of the land, or operate to create a new estate, and, if any conditions are attached to that`
  line `consent, those conditions shall be binding on the parties to the partition.`
  line
  line `(2) A partition of a tenancy shall not, without the express consent of the landlord, affect the joint`
  line `liability of the co-sharers therein for the payment of the rent thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (70984)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Application for partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70984&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `Any joint owner of land, or any joint tenant of a tenancy in which a`
  line `right of occupancy subsists, may apply to a Revenue-officer for partition of his share in the land or`
  line `tenancy, as the case may be, if—.`
  line
  line `(a) at the date of the application the share is recorded under Chapter IV as belonging to him, or.`
  line
  line `(b) his right to the share has been established by a decree which is still subsisting at the date, or.`
  line
  line `(c) a written acknowledgement of that right has been executed by all persons interested in the`
  line `admission or denial thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (70985)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Restrictions and limitations on partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70985&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in the last foregoing`
  line section—
  line
  line `(1) places of worship and burial grounds held in common before partition shall continue to be so held`
  line `after partition, unless the parties otherwise agree among themselves and record their agreement and file it`
  line `with the Revenue-officer;`
  line
  line `(2) partition of any of the following properties, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) any embankment, watercourse, well or tank, and any land on which the supply of water to any`
  line `such work may depend,`
  line
  line `(b) any grazing-ground, and`
  line
  line `(c) any land which is occupied as the site of a town or village and is assessed to land revenue;`
  line `may be refused if in the opinion of the Revenue-officer the partition of such property is likely to cause`
  line `inconvenience to the co-shares or other persons directly or indirectly interested therein or to diminish`
  line `the utility thereof to these persons;`
  line
  line `(3) the fact that a partition on the application of a joint owner of land would render necessary the`
  line `severance into two or more parts of the land comprised in the tenancy of a tenant having a right of`
  line `occupancy may, unless the tenant assents to the severance, be a sufficient reason for the disallowance of`
  line `the partition in so far as it would affect that tenancy; and`
  line
  line `(4) the fact that the landlord objects to the partition of a tenancy may be sufficient reason for the`
  line `absolute disallowance of the partition thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (70986)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Notice of application for partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70986&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `The Revenue-officer, on receiving the application under`
  line `section 111, shall, if it is in order and not open to objection on the face of it, fix a day for the hearing`
  line `thereof, and—`
  line
  line `(a) cause notice of the application and of the day so fixed to be served on such of the recorded`
  line `co-shares as have not joined in the application, and, if the share of which partition is applied for is a`
  line `share in a tenancy, on the landlord also; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he thinks fit, cause the notice to be served on, or proclaimed for the information of, any other`
  line `persons whom he may deem to be directly or indirectly interested in the application`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (70987)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Addition of parties to application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70987&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `On the day fixed for the hearing, or on any day to which`
  line `the hearing may be adjourned, the Revenue-officer shall ascertain whether any of the other co-sharers`
  line `desire the partition of their share also, and, if any of them so desire, he shall add them as applicants`
  line `for partition`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (70988)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Absolute disallowance of partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70988&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `After examining such of the co-shares and other persons`
  line `as may be present on that day, the Revenue-officer may, if he is of opinion that there is good and`
  line `sufficient cause why partition should be absolutely disallowed, refuse the application, recording the`
  line `grounds of his refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (70989)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Procedure on admission of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70989&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `If the Revenue-officer does not refuse the application`
  line `under the last foregoing section, he shall ascertain the question, if any, in dispute between any of the`
  line `persons interested, distinguishing between—`
  line
  line `(a) questions as to title in the property of which partition`
  line `is sought; and`
  line
  line `(b) questions as to the property to be divided, or the mode of making the partition.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (70990)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Disposal of questions as to title in property to be divided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70990&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) When there is a question as to`
  line `title in any of the property of which partition is sought, the Revenue-officer may decline to grant the`
  line `application for partition until the question has been determined by a competent Court, or he may himself`
  line `proceed to determine the question as though he were such a Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Revenue-officer himself proceeds to determine the question, the following rules shall`
  line `apply, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) If the question is one over which a Revenue Court has jurisdiction, the Revenue-officer shall`
  line `proceed as a Revenue Court under the provisions of the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (XVI of 1887).`
  line
  line `(b) If the question is one over which a Civil Court has jurisdiction, the procedure of the Revenueofficer shall be that applicable to the trial of an original suit by a Civil Court, and he shall record a`
  line `judgment and decree containing the particulars required by the Code of Civil Procedure to be specified`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(c) An appeal shall lie from the decree of the Revenue-officer under clause (b) as though that`
  line `decree were a decree of a district Judge in an original suit.`
  line
  line `(d) Upon such an appeal being made, the Divisional Court or Chief Court, as the case may be, may`
  line `issue an injunction to the Revenue-officer requiring him to stay proceeding pending the disposal of the`
  line appeal.
  line
  line `(e) From the appellate decree of a Divisional Court upon such an appeal a further appeal shall lie to`
  line `the Chief Court if such a further appeal is allowed by the law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (70991)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Disposal of other questions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70991&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) When there is a question as to the property to be divided, or`
  line `the mode of making a partition, the Revenue-officer shall, after, such inquiry as he deems necessary,`
  line `record an order stating his decision on the question and his reasons for the decision.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal may be preferred to the Commissioner from an order under sub-section (1) within`
  line `fifteen days from the date thereof, and, when such an appeal is preferred and the institution thereof has`
  line `been certified to the Revenue-officer by the Commissioner, the Revenue-officer shall stay proceedings`
  line `pending the disposal of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) If an applicant for partition is dissatisfied with an original or appellate order under this section, and`
  line `applies for permission to withdraw from the proceedings in so far as they relate to the partition of his`
  line `shares, he shall be permitted to withdraw therefrom on such terms as the Revenue-officer thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) When an applicant withdraw, under the last foregoing sub-section, the Revenue-officer may, where`
  line `the other applicants, if any, desire the continuance of the proceeding, continue them in so as far they`
  line `relate to the partition of the shares of those other applicants.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (70992)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Administration of property excluded from partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70992&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `When any such property as is referred`
  line `to in section 112, clause (2), is excluded from partition, the Revenue-officer may determine the extent and`
  line `manner to and in which the co-sharers and other persons interested therein may make use thereof, and the`
  line `proportion in which the expenditure incurred thereon and profits derived therefrom, respectively, are to be`
  line `borne by and divided among those persons or any of them.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (70993)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Distribution of revenue and rent after partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70993&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount of revenue to be paid in`
  line `respect of each of the holdings into which land has been divided on a partition, and the amount of rent to`
  line `be paid in respect of each of the portions into which a tenancy has been so divided, shall be determined by`
  line `the Revenue-officer making the partition.`
  line
  line `(2) The determination of the Revenue-officer as to the revenue to be paid in respect of each holding`
  line `shall, where the estate in which the holding is situate in subject to a fixed assessment, be deemed to be an`
  line `order under section 56, sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where new estates have been created at a partition and the land-revenue has been fraudulently or`
  line `erroneously distributed among them, the Local Government may, within twelve years from the time of`
  line `discovery of the fraud or error, order a new distribution of the land-revenue among the several estates, on`
  line `a estimate of the assets of each estate at the time of the partition, to be made conformably to the best`
  line `evidence and information procurable respecting the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (70994)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Instrument of partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70994&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `When a partition is completed, the Revenue-officer shall cause an`
  line `instrument of partition to be prepared, and the date on which the partition is to take effect to be recorded`
  line therein.
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (70995)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Delivery of possessions of property allotted on partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70995&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `An owner or tenant to whom any`
  line `land or portion of a tenancy, as the case may be, is allotted in proceedings for partition shall be entitled to`
  line `possession thereof as against the other parties to the proceedings and their legal representatives, and a`
  line `Revenue-officer shall, on application made to him for the purpose by any such owner or tenant at any`
  line `time within three years from the date recorded in the instrument of partition under the last foregoing`
  line `section, give effect to that instrument so far as it concerns the applicant as if it were a decree for`
  line `immovable property.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (70996)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Affirmation of partition s privately effected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70996&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any case in which a partition has been`
  line `made without the intervention of a Revenue-officer, any party thereto may apply to a Revenue-officer for`
  line `an order affirming the partition.`
  line
  line `(2) On receiving the application, the Revenue-officer shall inquire into the case, and, if he finds that`
  line `the partition has in fact been made, he may make an order affirming it and proceed under sections 119,`
  line `120, 121 and 122, or any of those sections, as circumstances may require, in the same manner as if the`
  line `partition had been made on an application to himself under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (70997)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Power to make rules as to costs of partition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70997&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `The Financial Commissioner may make rules`
  line `for determining the costs of partitions under this Chapter and the mode in which such costs are to be`
  line apportioned.
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (70998)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Re-distribution of land according to custom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70998&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `When by established custom any land in an`
  line `estate is subject to periodical re-distribution of a Revenue-officer may, on the application of any of the`
  line `land-owners, enforce the re-distribution according to the custom, and for this purpose may exercise all or`
  line `any of the powers of a Revenue-officer in proceedings, for partition`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (70999)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Officer who may be empowered to act under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=70999&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `The Revenue-officer by whom`
  line `proceedings may be taken under this Chapter shall be a Revenue-officer of a class not below that of`
  line `Assistant Collector of the first grade.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (71001)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Power to refer to arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71001&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Revenue-officer may, with the consent of the parties,`
  line `refer to arbitration any dispute arising before him in any`
  line `matter under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A Collector or any Assistant Collector of the first grade may, without the consent of the parties,`
  line `refer to arbitration any dispute before him with respect to—`
  line
  line `(a) any matter of which an entry is to be made in any record or register under Chapter IV;`
  line
  line `(b) any matter relating to the distribution of an assessment under section 56;`
  line
  line `(c) the limits of any estate or of any holding, field or other portion of an estate; or`
  line
  line `(d) the property to be divided at a partition or the mode of making a partition.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (71002)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Order of reference and contents thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71002&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) In referring a dispute to arbitration a`
  line `Revenue-officer shall make an order of reference, and specify therein the precise matter submitted toarbitration, the number of arbitrators which each party to the dispute is to nominate, the period within`
  line `which arbitrators are to be nominated, and the period within which the award is to`
  line `be delivered.`
  line
  line `(2) The number of arbitrators which each party may nominate must be the same and must not exceed`
  line two.
  line
  line `(3) If from any cause arbitrators are not nominated, or an award is not delivered, within the period`
  line `fixed therefor in the order of reference, the Revenue-officer may from time to time enlarge that period, or`
  line `may cancel the order of reference.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (71003)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Nomination of arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71003&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an order of reference has been made, the parties may`
  line `each nominate the number of arbitrators specified in the order, and the Revenue-officer shall nominate`
  line `one other arbitrator.`
  line
  line `(2) The Revenue-officer may, for reasons to be recorded by him, make an order disallowing any`
  line `nomination made by either party and requiring the party to make another nomination within a time to be`
  line `specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under the last foregoing sub-section shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (71004)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Substitution of arbitrators by parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71004&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `If an arbitrator nominated by the party dies, desires to`
  line `be discharged or refuses or becomes incapable to act, the party may nominate another person in his stead.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (71005)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Nomination and substitution of arbitrators by Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71005&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `In any of the following`
  line `cases, namely;`
  line
  line `(a) if either of the parties fails to nominate an arbitrator under sub-section (1) of section 129 within`
  line `the period fixed in the order of reference, or`
  line
  line `(b) if the nomination of an arbitrator has been disallowed under sub-section (2) of section 129, and`
  line `another arbitrator is no nominated within the time specified in the order under that sub-section or ,`
  line `having been so nominated, his nomination is also disallowed, or`
  line
  line `(c) if a party entitled to nominate an arbitrator in the place of another arbitrator under`
  line `section 130, fails to nominate him within one week from the date of the communication to him of a`
  line `notice requiring him to make the nomination, or`
  line
  line `(d) if an arbitrator nominated by the Revenue-officer dies, desires to be discharged or refuses or`
  line `becomes incapable to act,`
  line `the Revenue-officer may nominate a person as arbitrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (71006)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Process for appearance before arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71006&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Revenue-officer shall, on the application`
  line `of the arbitrators, issue the same processes to the parties and witnesses whom the arbitrators desire to`
  line `examine as he may issue in any proceeding under this Act before himself.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such party or witness shall be bound to appear before the arbitrators in obedience to a process`
  line `issued under sub-section (1), either in person or by agent, as the arbitrators may require.`
  line
  line `(3) The person attending in obedience to the process shall be bound to state the truth upon any matter`
  line `respecting which he is examined or makes statements, and to produce such documents and other things`
  line `relating to any such matter as may be specified in the process.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (71007)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Award of arbitrators and presentation thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71007&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) The arbitrators shall make an award in`
  line `writing under their hands concerning the matters referred to them for arbitration, and state therein their`
  line `reasons therefor, and any arbitrator dissenting from the award made by a majority of the arbitrators shall`
  line `state the grounds of his dissent.`
  line
  line `(2) The arbitrators shall present the award to the Revenue-officer in person unless that officer permits`
  line `them to present it by agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (71008)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Procedure on presentation of award.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71008&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the award has been received, the Revenueofficer shall, if the parties are present, consider forthwith any objection which they may have to make`
  line `thereto, and, if they are not present, fix a date for the consideration thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a date has been fixed for the consideration of an award, the Revenue-officer shall on that`
  line `date, or on any subsequent date to which an adjournment may be made, hear any objections which the`
  line `parties may have to make to the award.`
  line
  line `(3) The Revenue-officer may also, if he thinks fit, question the arbitrators as to the grounds of their`
  line award.
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (71009)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Effect of award.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71009&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Revenue-officer may accept, modify or reject the award, recording his`
  line `reasons for doing so in his decision respecting the dispute`
  line `which was referred to arbitration.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal shall lie from the decision as if arbitrators had not been appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (71035)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Power to invest officers making records-of-rights or general re-assessments with powers of Civil Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71035&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may, by order published in the official Gazette, invest any`
  line `Revenue-officer making or specially revising records-of-rights in any local area in pursuance of a`
  line `notification under section 32 or making re-assessment of land-revenue in any local area in pursuance of a`
  line `notification under section 49, or any Revenue-officer to whose control that officer is subject, with all or`
  line `any of the powers of any Court constituted under the Punjab Courts Act, 1884 (XVIII of 1884), for the`
  line `purpose of trying all or any specified classes of suits or appeals relating to land arising in the local area.`
  line
  line `(2) The Local Government may cancel an order under sub-section (1) wholly or in part.`
  line
  line `(3) While an order or any part of an order under that sub-section continues in force, the powers`
  line `conferred thereby shall be exercised by the officer invested therewith and not otherwise.`
  line
  line `(4) Any cases pending before that officer under the order or a subsisting part of the order at the time of`
  line `cancellation thereof may be disposed of by him as if the order or that part of it continued in force, unless`
  line `the Local Government directs, as it is hereby empowered to do, that those cases shall be transferred for`
  line `disposal to the Courts by which they would have been disposed of if the order had not been published.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (71011)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Control over such officers and appeals from and revision of their decrees and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71011&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may by notification direct that the provisions of this Act with`
  line `respect to the superintendence and control over Revenue-officers shall, subject to any modification of`
  line `those provisions which the Local Government thinks fit, apply to any Revenue-officer, except the Financial Commissioner, who has been invested with the powers of a Civil Court of any of the classes`
  line `specified in clauses (a) , (b), (c) and (d) of section 17 of the Punjab Courts Act, 1884 (XVIII of 1884),`
  line `and that appeals shall lie from his decrees and orders to, and his decrees and orders be subject to revision`
  line `by, a Revenue-officer invested under the last foregoing section with the powers of a Court which would`
  line `be competent under the Punjab Courts Act, 1884, to hear appeals from, or revise, such decrees and orders`
  line `if they had been made by a Court with the powers of which the Revenue-officer who made them has been`
  line invested.
  line
  line `(2) In the absence of any such notification, a Revenue-officer invested under the last foregoing section`
  line `with the powers of any such Civil Court as aforesaid shall, with respect to the exercise of those powers,`
  line `be deemed to be such a Civil Court for the purpose of the Punjab Courts Act, 1884.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (71013)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Power to deposit certain sums other than rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71013&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) In either of the following cases,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) when a headman or other landowner, or an assignee of land-revenue, to whom any sum other`
  line `than rent is payable on account of a liability under this Act refuses to receive the sum from, or to grant`
  line `a receipt therefor to, the person by whom it is payable,`
  line
  line `(b) when the person by whom any such sum is payable is in doubt as to the headman or other`
  line `landowner, or the assignee of land-revenue, entitled to receive it.`
  line `that person may apply to a Revenue-officer for leave to deposit the sum in his office, and the`
  line `Revenue-officer shall receive the deposit if, after examining the applicant, he is satisfied that there is`
  line `sufficient ground for the application, and if the applicant pays the fee, if any, which may be chargeable`
  line `on any notice to be issued of the receipt thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) When a deposit has been so received, the liability of the depositor to the headman or other landowner, or the assignee of land–revenue, for the amount thereof shall be discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (71014)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Procedure in case of deposit on account of a payment due to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71014&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `If the deposit`
  line `purports to be made on account of any payment due to the Government, it may be credited accordingly`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (71015)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Procedure in case of other deposits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71015&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue-officer receiving a deposit purporting to`
  line `be made on any other account shall give notice of the receipt thereof to every person who he has reason to`
  line `believe claims or is entitled to the deposit, and may pay the amount thereof to any person appearing to`
  line `him to be entitled to the same, or may, if he thinks fit, retain the deposit pending the decision of a Civil`
  line `Court as to the person so entitled.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other proceeding shall be instituted against the Secretary of State for India in Council, or`
  line `against any officer of the Government, in respect of anything done by a Revenue-officer under this`
  line `section, but nothing in this sub-section shall prevent any person entitled to receive the amount of any such`
  line `deposit from recovering it from a person to whom it has been paid by a Revenue-officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (71039)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Orders of Civil and Criminal Courts for execution of processes against land or the produce thereof to be addressed to a Revenue-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71039&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `Orders issued by any Civil or Criminal Court for the`
  line `attachment, sale or delivery of any land or interest in land, or for the attachment or sale of the produce of`
  line `any land, shall be addressed to the Collector or such Revenue-officer as the Collector may appoint in this`
  line `behalf, and be executed by the Collector or that officer in accordance with the provisions of the law`
  line `applicable to the Court issuing the orders and with any rules consistent there with made by the Financial`
  line `Commissioner with the concurrence of the Chief Court and the previous sanction of the Local`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (71017)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Attachment of assigned land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71017&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) Not withstanding anything in any other enactment`
  line `for the time being in force, an order issued by any Court for the attachment of assigned land-revenue shall`
  line `require the person by whom the revenue is payable to pay it to the Collector, and the Collector to hold it`
  line `subject to the further orders of the court.`
  line
  line `(2) A payment to the Collector under sub-section (1) shall be an effectual discharge to the person`
  line `making it`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (71018)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Preservation of attached produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71018&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) The attachment of the produce of any land in`
  line `pursuance of an order of any Court or other authority shall not prevent the person to whom the produce`
  line `belongs from reaping, gathering or storing it or doing any other act necessary for its preservation.`
  line
  line `(2) The attaching officer shall do or cause to be done all acts necessary for the preservation of the`
  line `produce if the person to whom it belongs fails to do so.`
  line
  line `(3) When sale of produce follows on its attachment, the purchaser shall be entitled, by himself or by`
  line `any person appointed by him in his behalf, to enter on the place where the produce is and do all that is`
  line `necessary for the purpose of preserving and removing it.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (71019)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Division of produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71019&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `In either of the following cases, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) where land-revenue is paid by`
  line `division or appraisement of the produce,`
  line
  line `(b) where a superior and an inferior landowner, or two or more shareholders in a holding or`
  line `tenancy, are jointly interested in any produce, and either or any of the landowners or tenants, as the`
  line `case may be, desires the assistance of a Revenue-officer for the purpose of dividing or appraising the`
  line `produce, the provisions of the Punjab Tenancy Act, 1887 (XVI of 1887), with respect to the division`
  line `or appraisement of produce shall apply so far as they can be made applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (71020)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Village cesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71020&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any of the following times, namely:-`
  line
  line `(a) when a record-of-rights is being made or specially revised for an estate,`
  line
  line `(b) when the local area in which an estate is situate is being generally re-assessed and before the`
  line `assessment has been confirmed,`
  line
  line `(c) at any other time on an order made with respect to any estate by the Local Government with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Governor General in Council,`
  line
  line `a Revenue-officer shall prepare a list of village-cesses, if any, levied in the estate which have been`
  line `generally or specially approved by the Local Government, or the title to which has before the passing of`
  line `this Act been judicially established.`
  line
  line `(2) When a list has been prepared for an estate under sub-section (1), a village-cess not comprised`
  line `therein shall not be recoverable by suit in any Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The Local Government may impose on the collection of any village-cess comprised in the list such`
  line `conditions as to police or other establishments connected with the village, market or fair in or on account`
  line `of which the cess is levied, as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Governor General in Council may, on a reference from the Local Government, declare`
  line `weather any cess, contribution or due levied in an estate is or is not a village-cess.`
  line
  line `(5) A declaration of the Governor General in Council under the last foregoing sub-section shall be`
  line `conclusive, and shall not be liable to be questioned in any Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (71021)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Superior land-owners’ dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71021&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `Where a superior landowner is entitled to receive in respect of`
  line `any land from an inferior landowner dues in kind or in cash of fluctuating quantity or amount, the`
  line `Collector may—`
  line
  line `(a) on the application of both landowners, or`
  line
  line `(b) with the previous sanction of the Local Government, on the application either of them,`
  line `commute those dues into a fixed percentage of the land-revenue payable by the inferior landowner in`
  line `respect of the land`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (71022)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Substitution of service for payment of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71022&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Local Government may, with`
  line `the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council, authorize the remission of land-revenue in`
  line `whole or in part in consideration of the person liable therefor undertaking to render in lieu thereof such`
  line `public service as may be specified in an agreement to be approved by the Local Government and executed`
  line `by that person.`
  line
  line `(2) The Local Government may, with the like sanction, cancel any remission authorized, and`
  line `agreement made, under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) If a landowner bound by an agreement under that sub-section to render public service in lieu of`
  line `paying land-revenue fails, to render the service to the satisfaction of the collector, the collector may`
  line `determine the portion of the land-revenue remitted which is represented by the service in respect of which`
  line `the landowner is in default, and, with the previous sanction of the financial Commissioner, recover that`
  line `portion as if it were an arrear of land-revenue due in respect of the land for the land-revenue whereof the`
  line `service was substituted`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (71023)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Recovery of cost of assessing assigned land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71023&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) When land of which the landrevenue has been assigned in whole or in part is re-assessed, the assignee shall be liable to pay such a`
  line `share of the cost of making the re-assessment as the Financial Commissioner may determine to be just.`
  line
  line `(2) That share may be recovered by the Collector by the deduction of the amount thereof from the`
  line `land-revenue due to the assignee.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (71024)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Penalty for failure to attend within limits of estate in obedience to order of Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71024&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `If a person required by a summons, notice, order or proclamation proceeding from a Revenueofficer to attend at a certain time and place within the limits of the estate in which he ordinarily resides, or`
  line `in which he holds or cultivates land, fails to comply with the requisition, he shall be liable at the`
  line `discretion of the Revenue-officer to fine which may extend to fifty rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (71025)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Prevention of encroachment on common lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71025&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where land which has been reserved for`
  line `the common purposes of the co-sharers therein has been encroached on by any co-sharer, a Revenueofficer may, on the application of any other co-sharer, eject the encroaching co-sharer from the land and,`
  line `by order proclaimed in manner mentioned in section 22, forbid`
  line `repetition of the encroachment.`
  line
  line `(2) The proceedings of the Revenue-officer under sub-section (1) shall be subject to any decree or`
  line `order which may be subsequently passed by any Court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (71026)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Papers kept by village-officers to be deemed public documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71026&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any record or paper`
  line `which a village-officer is required by law, or by any rule under this Act, to prepare or keep shall be`
  line `deemed to be the property of the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A village-officer shall, with respect to any such record or paper in his custody, be deemed for the`
  line `purposes of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (I of 1872), to be a public officer having the custody of a`
  line `public document which any person has a right to inspect.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (71027)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title Costs.
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71027&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue-officer may give and apportion the costs of any proceeding under this`
  line `Act in any manner he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) But if he orders that the cost of any such proceeding shall not follow the event, he shall record his`
  line `reasons for the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (71028)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Computation of periods limited for appeals and applications for review.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71028&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `In the computation`
  line `of the period for an appeal from, or an application for the review of, an order under this Act the limitation`
  line `therefor shall be governed by the Indian Limitation Act, 1877 (XV of 1877).`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (71029)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Restriction on Revenue-officers bidding at auctions or trading.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71029&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Revenue-officer, or a`
  line `person employed in a revenue-office, shall not—`
  line
  line `(a) purchase or bid for, either in person or by agent, in his own name or in that of another, or jointly`
  line `or in shares with others, any property which any Revenue-officer or Revenue Court in the District in`
  line `which he is employed has ordered to be sold, or,`
  line
  line `(b) in contravention of any rules made by the Local Government in this behalf, engage in trade in`
  line `that district.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to preclude any person from becoming a member of a`
  line `company incorporated under the Indian Companies Act, 1882, (VI of 1882) or other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (71030)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71030&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Financial Commissioner may, in addition to other rules which`
  line `may be made by him under this Act, make rules consistent with this Act, and any other enactment for the`
  line `time being in force—`
  line
  line `(a) fixing the number and amount of the installments, and the times and places and the manner, by,`
  line `at and in which any sum other than rent or land-revenue which is payable under this Act or of which a`
  line `record has been made there under is to be paid;`
  line
  line `(b) fixing the dates on which profits are to be divisible by headman or other persons by whom they`
  line `are realized on behalf of co-sharers;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the fees to be charged for the service and execution of processes issued by`
  line `Revenue-officers and Revenue Courts, the mode in which those fees are to be collected, the number of`
  line `persons to be employed in the service and execution of those processes, and the remuneration and`
  line `duties of those persons;`
  line
  line `(d) regulating the procedure in the cases where persons are entitled to inspect records of Revenueofficers, or records or papers in the custody of village-officer, or to obtain copies of the same, and`
  line `prescribing the fees payable for searches and copies;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribing forms for such books, entries, statistics and accounts as the Financial Commissioner`
  line `thinks necessary to be kept, made or compiled in revenue-offices or submitted to any authority;`
  line
  line `(f) declaring what shall be the language of any of those offices, and determining in what cases`
  line `persons practising in those offices shall be permitted to address the presiding officers thereof in`
  line `English; and`
  line
  line `(g) generally for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Until rules are made under clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1) the sums therein referred to shall`
  line `be payable by the installments, at the times and places, and in the manner by, at and in which they are`
  line `now payable.`
  line
  line `(3) Rules made by the Financial Commissioner under this or any other section of this Act shall not`
  line `take effect until they have been sanctioned by the Local Government, and rules under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall not take effect until they have also been confirmed by the Governor General in`
  line Council.
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (71031)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Rules to be made after previous publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71031&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `The power to make any rules under this Act is`
  line `subject to the control of the Governor General in Council, and to the condition of the rules being made`
  line `after previous publication:`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (71032)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Powers exerciseable by the Financial Commissioner from time to time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71032&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `All powers`
  line `conferred by this Act on The Financial Commissioner may be exercised from time to time as occasion`
  line requires.
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (71033)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Exclusion of jurisdiction of Civil Courts, in matters within the jurisdiction of Revenue-officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751&sectionId=71033&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00005_188717_1667972973751
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise provided by this Act—`
  line
  line `(1) a Civil Court shall not have jurisdiction in any matter which the Local Government or a Revenueofficer is empowered by this Act to dispose of, or take cognizance of the manner in which the Local`
  line `Government or any Revenue-officer exercises any powers vested in it or him by or under this Act; and in`
  line particular—
  line
  line `(2) a Civil Court shall not exercise jurisdiction over any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) any question as to the limits of any land which has been defined by a Revenue-officer as land to`
  line `which this Act does or does not apply;`
  line
  line `(ii) any claim to compel the performance of any duties imposed by this Act or any other enactment`
  line `for the time being in force on any Revenue-officer, as such;`
  line
  line `(iii) any claim to the office of kanungo, zaildar, inamdar or village-officer, or in respect of any`
  line `injury caused by exclusion from such office, or to compel the performance of the duties or a division`
  line `of the emoluments thereof ;`
  line
  line `(iv) any notification directing the making or revision of`
  line `a record-of-rights;`
  line
  line `(v) the framing of a record-of-rights or annual record, or the preparation, signing or attestation of`
  line `any of the documents included in such a record;`
  line
  line `(vi) the correction of any entry in a record-of-rights, annual record or register of mutations;`
  line
  line `(vii) any notification of the undertaking of the general re-assessment of a district or tahsil having`
  line `been sanctioned by the Governor General in Council;`
  line
  line `(viii) the claim of any person to be liable for an assessment of land-revenue or of any other revenue`
  line `assessed under this Act ;`
  line
  line `(ix) the amount of land-revenue to be assessed on any estate or to be paid in respect of any holding`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(x) the amount of, or the liability of any person to pay, any other revenue to be assessed under this Act,`
  line `or any cess, charge or rate to be assessed on an estate or holding under this Act or any other enactment for`
  line `the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(xi) any claim relating to the allowance to be received by a landowner who has given notice of his`
  line `refusal to be liable for an assessment, or any claim connected with, or arising out of, any proceedings taken`
  line `in consequence of the refusal of any person to be liable for an`
  line `assessment under this Act;`
  line `(xii) the formation of an estate out of waste land;`
  line `(xiii) any claim to hold free of revenue any land, mills, fisheries or natural products of land or`
  line water;
  line `(xiv) any claim connected with, or arising out of, the collection by the Government, or the enforcement`
  line `by the Government of any process for the recovery, of land-revenue or any sum recoverable as an arrear of`
  line land-revenue;
  line `(xv) any claim to set aside, on any ground other than fraud, a sale for the recovery of an arrear of landrevenue or any sum recoverable as an arrear of land-revenue;`
  line `(xvi) the amount of, or the liability of any person to pay, any fees, fines, costs or other charges imposed`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xvii) any claim for partition of an estate, holding or tenancy, or any question connected with, or arising`
  line `out of, proceedings for partition, not being a question as to title in any of the property of which partition is`
  line sought;
  line
  line `(xviii) any question as to the allotment of land on the partition of an estate, holding or tenancy, or as to`
  line `the distribution of land subject by established custom to periodical re-distribution, or as to the distribution`
  line `of land-revenue on the partition of an estate or holding or on a periodical re-distribution of land, or as to the`
  line `distribution of rent on the partition of a tenancy;`
  line
  line `(xix) any claim to set aside or disturb a division or appraisement of produce confirmed or verified by a`
  line `Revenue-officer under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xx) any question relating to the preparation of a list of village-cesses or the imposition by the Local`
  line `Government of conditions on the collection of such cesses;`
  line
  line `(xxi) any proceeding under this Act for the commutation of the dues of a superior land-owner;`
  line
  line `(xxii) any claim arising out of the enforcement of an agreement to render public service in lieu of paying`
  line `land-revenue; or`
  line
  line `(xxiii) any claim arising out of the liability of an assignee of land-revenue to pay a share of the cost of`
  line `collecting or re-assessing such revenue, or arising out of the liability of an assignee to pay out of assigned`
  line `land-revenue, or of a person who would be liable for land-revenue if it had not been released, compounded`
  line `for or redeemed to pay on the land-revenue for which he would but for such release, composition or`
  line `redemption be liable, such a percentage for the remuneration of a zaildar, inamdar or village-officer as may`
  line `be prescribed by rules for the time being in force under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
